69 /*
70  * fetch_peek_arith () -
71  * return: NO_ERROR or ER_code
72  * regu_var(in/out): Regulator Variable of an ARITH node.
73  * vd(in): Value Descriptor
74  * obj_oid(in): Object Identifier
75  * tpl(in): Tuple
76  * peek_dbval(out): Set to the value resulting from the fetch operation
77  */
78 static int
79 fetch_peek_arith (THREAD_ENTRY * thread_p, REGU_VARIABLE * regu_var, VAL_DESCR * vd, OID * obj_oid, QFILE_TUPLE tpl,
80  DB_VALUE ** peek_dbval)
81 {
82  ARITH_TYPE *arithptr;
83  DB_VALUE *peek_left, *peek_right, *peek_third, *peek_fourth;
84  DB_VALUE tmp_value;
85  TP_DOMAIN *original_domain = NULL;
86  TP_DOMAIN_STATUS dom_status;
87 
88  assert (regu_var != NULL);
89  arithptr = regu_var->value.arithptr;
90  if (REGU_VARIABLE_IS_FLAGED (regu_var, REGU_VARIABLE_FETCH_ALL_CONST))
91  {
92  *peek_dbval = arithptr->value;
93 
94  return NO_ERROR;
95  }
96 
97  assert (!REGU_VARIABLE_IS_FLAGED (regu_var, REGU_VARIABLE_FETCH_ALL_CONST));
98 
99  peek_left = NULL;
100  peek_right = NULL;
101  peek_third = NULL;
102  peek_fourth = NULL;
103 
104  if (thread_get_recursion_depth (thread_p) > prm_get_integer_value (PRM_ID_MAX_RECURSION_SQL_DEPTH))
105  {
106  int error = ER_MAX_RECURSION_SQL_DEPTH;
107  er_set (ER_ERROR_SEVERITY, ARG_FILE_LINE, error, 1, prm_get_integer_value (PRM_ID_MAX_RECURSION_SQL_DEPTH));
108  return error;
109  }
110  thread_inc_recursion_depth (thread_p);
111 
112  /* fetch values */
113  switch (arithptr->opcode)
114  {
115  case T_SUBSTRING:
116  case T_LPAD:
117  case T_RPAD:
118  case T_REPLACE:
119  case T_TRANSLATE:
120  case T_TO_CHAR:
121  case T_TO_DATE:
122  case T_TO_TIME:
123  case T_TO_TIMESTAMP:
124  case T_TO_DATETIME:
125  case T_TO_NUMBER:
126  case T_INSTR:
127  case T_MID:
128  case T_DATE_ADD:
129  case T_DATE_SUB:
130  case T_NEXT_VALUE:
131  case T_INDEX_PREFIX:
132  case T_TO_DATETIME_TZ:
133  case T_TO_TIMESTAMP_TZ:
134 
135  /* fetch lhs, rhs, and third value */
136  if (fetch_peek_dbval (thread_p, arithptr->leftptr, vd, NULL, obj_oid, tpl, &peek_left) != NO_ERROR)
137  {
138  goto error;
139  }
140  if (!DB_IS_NULL (peek_left))
141  {
142  if (fetch_peek_dbval (thread_p, arithptr->rightptr, vd, NULL, obj_oid, tpl, &peek_right) != NO_ERROR)
143  {
144  goto error;
145  }
146  if ((prm_get_integer_value (PRM_ID_COMPAT_MODE) == COMPAT_MYSQL || arithptr->opcode == T_SUBSTRING)
147  && !arithptr->thirdptr)
148  {
149  break;
150  }
151  if (arithptr->thirdptr != NULL)
152  {
153  if (fetch_peek_dbval (thread_p, arithptr->thirdptr, vd, NULL, obj_oid, tpl, &peek_third) != NO_ERROR)
154  {
155  goto error;
156  }
157  }
158  }
159  break;
160 
161  case T_STR_TO_DATE:
162  case T_DATE_FORMAT:
163  case T_TIME_FORMAT:
164  case T_FORMAT:
165  if (fetch_peek_dbval (thread_p, arithptr->thirdptr, vd, NULL, obj_oid, tpl, &peek_third) != NO_ERROR)
166  {
167  goto error;
168  }
169  case T_ADD:
170  case T_SUB:
171  case T_MUL:
172  case T_DIV:
173  case T_MOD:
174  case T_POSITION:
175  case T_FINDINSET:
176  case T_ADD_MONTHS:
177  case T_MONTHS_BETWEEN:
178  case T_AES_ENCRYPT:
179  case T_AES_DECRYPT:
180  case T_SHA_TWO:
181  case T_POWER:
182  case T_ROUND:
183  case T_LOG:
184  case T_TRUNC:
185  case T_STRCAT:
186  case T_NULLIF:
187  case T_INCR:
188  case T_DECR:
189  case T_BIT_AND:
190  case T_BIT_OR:
191  case T_BIT_XOR:
192  case T_BITSHIFT_LEFT:
193  case T_BITSHIFT_RIGHT:
194  case T_INTDIV:
195  case T_INTMOD:
196  case T_STRCMP:
197  case T_ATAN2:
198  case T_ADDDATE:
199  case T_SUBDATE:
200  case T_DATEDIFF:
201  case T_TIMEDIFF:
202  case T_CURRENT_VALUE:
203  case T_CHR:
204  case T_JSON_EXTRACT:
205  /* fetch lhs and rhs value */
206  if (fetch_peek_dbval (thread_p, arithptr->leftptr, vd, NULL, obj_oid, tpl, &peek_left) != NO_ERROR)
207  {
208  goto error;
209  }
210  if (DB_IS_NULL (peek_left))
211  {
212  if (prm_get_bool_value (PRM_ID_ORACLE_STYLE_EMPTY_STRING)
213  && (arithptr->opcode == T_STRCAT || arithptr->opcode == T_ADD))
214  {
215  /* check for result type. */
216  if (TP_DOMAIN_TYPE (regu_var->domain) == DB_TYPE_VARIABLE
217  || QSTR_IS_ANY_CHAR_OR_BIT (TP_DOMAIN_TYPE (regu_var->domain)))
218  {
219  if (fetch_peek_dbval (thread_p, arithptr->rightptr, vd, NULL, obj_oid, tpl, &peek_right) != NO_ERROR)
220  {
221  goto error;
222  }
223  }
224  }
225  }
226  else
227  {
228  if (fetch_peek_dbval (thread_p, arithptr->rightptr, vd, NULL, obj_oid, tpl, &peek_right) != NO_ERROR)
229  {
230  goto error;
231  }
232  }
233  break;
234 
235  case T_TRIM:
236  case T_LTRIM:
237  case T_RTRIM:
238  /* fetch lhs and rhs value */
239  if (fetch_peek_dbval (thread_p, arithptr->leftptr, vd, NULL, obj_oid, tpl, &peek_left) != NO_ERROR)
240  {
241  goto error;
242  }
243  if (arithptr->rightptr != NULL)
244  {
245  if (fetch_peek_dbval (thread_p, arithptr->rightptr, vd, NULL, obj_oid, tpl, &peek_right) != NO_ERROR)
246  {
247  goto error;
248  }
249  }
250  break;
251 
252  case T_FROM_UNIXTIME:
253 
254  if (fetch_peek_dbval (thread_p, arithptr->leftptr, vd, NULL, obj_oid, tpl, &peek_left) != NO_ERROR)
255  {
256  goto error;
257  }
258  if (arithptr->rightptr != NULL)
259  {
260  if (fetch_peek_dbval (thread_p, arithptr->rightptr, vd, NULL, obj_oid, tpl, &peek_right) != NO_ERROR)
261  {
262  goto error;
263  }
264  }
265  if (arithptr->thirdptr != NULL)
266  {
267  if (fetch_peek_dbval (thread_p, arithptr->thirdptr, vd, NULL, obj_oid, tpl, &peek_third) != NO_ERROR)
268  {
269  goto error;
270  }
271  }
272  break;
273 
274  case T_SUBSTRING_INDEX:
275  case T_CONCAT_WS:
276  case T_FIELD:
277  case T_INDEX_CARDINALITY:
278  if (fetch_peek_dbval (thread_p, arithptr->leftptr, vd, NULL, obj_oid, tpl, &peek_left) != NO_ERROR)
279  {
280  goto error;
281  }
282  if (arithptr->rightptr != NULL)
283  {
284  if (fetch_peek_dbval (thread_p, arithptr->rightptr, vd, NULL, obj_oid, tpl, &peek_right) != NO_ERROR)
285  {
286  goto error;
287  }
288  }
289  if (fetch_peek_dbval (thread_p, arithptr->thirdptr, vd, NULL, obj_oid, tpl, &peek_third) != NO_ERROR)
290  {
291  goto error;
292  }
293  break;
294 
295  case T_CONV:
296  if (fetch_peek_dbval (thread_p, arithptr->leftptr, vd, NULL, obj_oid, tpl, &peek_left) != NO_ERROR)
297  {
298  goto error;
299  }
300  if (fetch_peek_dbval (thread_p, arithptr->rightptr, vd, NULL, obj_oid, tpl, &peek_right) != NO_ERROR)
301  {
302  goto error;
303  }
304  if (fetch_peek_dbval (thread_p, arithptr->thirdptr, vd, NULL, obj_oid, tpl, &peek_third) != NO_ERROR)
305  {
306  goto error;
307  }
308  break;
309 
310  case T_LOCATE:
311  if (fetch_peek_dbval (thread_p, arithptr->leftptr, vd, NULL, obj_oid, tpl, &peek_left) != NO_ERROR)
312  {
313  goto error;
314  }
315  if (fetch_peek_dbval (thread_p, arithptr->rightptr, vd, NULL, obj_oid, tpl, &peek_right) != NO_ERROR)
316  {
317  goto error;
318  }
319  if (arithptr->thirdptr != NULL)
320  {
321  if (fetch_peek_dbval (thread_p, arithptr->thirdptr, vd, NULL, obj_oid, tpl, &peek_third) != NO_ERROR)
322  {
323  goto error;
324  }
325  }
326  break;
327 
328  case T_CONCAT:
329  if (fetch_peek_dbval (thread_p, arithptr->leftptr, vd, NULL, obj_oid, tpl, &peek_left) != NO_ERROR)
330  {
331  goto error;
332  }
333  if (DB_IS_NULL (peek_left))
334  {
335  if (prm_get_bool_value (PRM_ID_ORACLE_STYLE_EMPTY_STRING))
336  {
337  if (arithptr->rightptr != NULL)
338  {
339  if (fetch_peek_dbval (thread_p, arithptr->rightptr, vd, NULL, obj_oid, tpl, &peek_right) != NO_ERROR)
340  {
341  goto error;
342  }
343  }
344  }
345  }
346  else
347  {
348  if (arithptr->rightptr != NULL)
349  {
350  if (fetch_peek_dbval (thread_p, arithptr->rightptr, vd, NULL, obj_oid, tpl, &peek_right) != NO_ERROR)
351  {
352  goto error;
353  }
354  }
355  }
356  break;
357 
358  case T_REPEAT:
359  case T_LEAST:
360  case T_GREATEST:
361  case T_SYS_CONNECT_BY_PATH:
362  case T_LEFT:
363  case T_RIGHT:
364  /* fetch both lhs and rhs value */
365  if (fetch_peek_dbval (thread_p, arithptr->leftptr, vd, NULL, obj_oid, tpl, &peek_left) != NO_ERROR)
366  {
367  goto error;
368  }
369  if (fetch_peek_dbval (thread_p, arithptr->rightptr, vd, NULL, obj_oid, tpl, &peek_right) != NO_ERROR)
370  {
371  goto error;
372  }
373  break;
374 
375  case T_MAKEDATE:
376  case T_ADDTIME:
377  case T_WEEK:
378  case T_DEFINE_VARIABLE:
379  case T_FROM_TZ:
380  /* fetch both lhs and rhs value */
381  if (fetch_peek_dbval (thread_p, arithptr->leftptr, vd, NULL, obj_oid, tpl, &peek_left) != NO_ERROR)
382  {
383  if (is_argument_wrapped_with_cast_op (arithptr->leftptr))
384  {
385  /* cast might have failed: set ER_DATE_CONVERSION */
386  er_set (ER_ERROR_SEVERITY, ARG_FILE_LINE, ER_DATE_CONVERSION, 0);
387  }
388  goto error;
389  }
390  if (fetch_peek_dbval (thread_p, arithptr->rightptr, vd, NULL, obj_oid, tpl, &peek_right) != NO_ERROR)
391  {
392  if (is_argument_wrapped_with_cast_op (arithptr->rightptr))
393  {
394  /* cast might have failed: set ER_DATE_CONVERSION */
395  er_set (ER_ERROR_SEVERITY, ARG_FILE_LINE, ER_DATE_CONVERSION, 0);
396  }
397  goto error;
398  }
399  break;
400 
401  case T_MAKETIME:
402  case T_NEW_TIME:
403  if (fetch_peek_dbval (thread_p, arithptr->leftptr, vd, NULL, obj_oid, tpl, &peek_left) != NO_ERROR)
404  {
405  if (is_argument_wrapped_with_cast_op (arithptr->leftptr))
406  {
407  /* cast might have failed: set ER_TIME_CONVERSION */
408  er_set (ER_ERROR_SEVERITY, ARG_FILE_LINE, ER_TIME_CONVERSION, 0);
409  }
410  goto error;
411  }
412  if (fetch_peek_dbval (thread_p, arithptr->rightptr, vd, NULL, obj_oid, tpl, &peek_right) != NO_ERROR)
413  {
414  if (is_argument_wrapped_with_cast_op (arithptr->rightptr))
415  {
416  /* cast might have failed: set ER_TIME_CONVERSION */
417  er_set (ER_ERROR_SEVERITY, ARG_FILE_LINE, ER_TIME_CONVERSION, 0);
418  }
419  goto error;
420  }
421  if (fetch_peek_dbval (thread_p, arithptr->thirdptr, vd, NULL, obj_oid, tpl, &peek_third) != NO_ERROR)
422  {
423  if (is_argument_wrapped_with_cast_op (arithptr->thirdptr))
424  {
425  /* cast might have failed: set ER_TIME_CONVERSION */
426  er_set (ER_ERROR_SEVERITY, ARG_FILE_LINE, ER_TIME_CONVERSION, 0);
427  }
428  goto error;
429  }
430  break;
431 
432  case T_CASE:
433  case T_DECODE:
434  case T_IF:
435  case T_IFNULL:
436  case T_NVL:
437  case T_PREDICATE:
438  case T_COALESCE:
439  case T_NVL2:
440  /* defer fetch values */
441  break;
442 
443  case T_LAST_DAY:
444 #if defined(ENABLE_UNUSED_FUNCTION)
445  case T_UNPLUS:
446 #endif /* ENABLE_UNUSED_FUNCTION */
447  case T_UNMINUS:
448  case T_OCTET_LENGTH:
449  case T_BIT_LENGTH:

4337 /*
4338  * fetch_peek_dbval_pos () -
4339  * return: NO_ERROR or ER_code
4340  * regu_var(in/out): Regulator Variable
4341  * tpl(in): Tuple
4342  * pos(in):
4343  * peek_dbval(out): Set to the value ref resulting from the fetch operation
4344  * next_tpl(out): Set to the next tuple ref
4345  */
4346 static int
4347 fetch_peek_dbval_pos (REGU_VARIABLE * regu_var, QFILE_TUPLE tpl, int pos, DB_VALUE ** peek_dbval,
4348  QFILE_TUPLE * next_tpl)
4349 {
4350  int length;
4351  PR_TYPE *pr_type;
4352  OR_BUF buf;
4353  char *ptr;
4354  QFILE_TUPLE_VALUE_POSITION *pos_descr;
4355 
4356  /* assume regu_var->type == TYPE_POSITION */
4357  pos_descr = &regu_var->value.pos_descr;
4358  pr_clear_value (regu_var->vfetch_to);
4359  *peek_dbval = regu_var->vfetch_to;
4360 
4361  /* locate value position in the tuple */
4362  if (qfile_locate_tuple_value_r (tpl, pos, &ptr, &length) == V_BOUND)
4363  {
4364  pr_type = pos_descr->dom->type;
4365  if (pr_type == NULL)
4366  {
4367  return ER_FAILED;
4368  }
4369 
4370  OR_BUF_INIT (buf, ptr, length);
4371  /* read value from the tuple */
4372  if ((*(pr_type->data_readval)) (&buf, *peek_dbval, pos_descr->dom, -1, false /* Don't copy */ ,
4373  NULL, 0) != NO_ERROR)
4374  {
4375  return ER_FAILED;
4376  }
4377  }
4378 
4379  /* next position pointer */
4380  *next_tpl = ptr + length;
4381 
4382  return NO_ERROR;
4383 }

4405

4481 /*
4482  * fetch_copy_dbval () - returns a COPY of a db_value which the caller
4483  * must clear
4484  * return: NO_ERROR or ER_code
4485  * regu_var(in/out): Regulator Variable
4486  * vd(in): Value Descriptor
4487  * cls_oid(in): Class Identifier
4488  * obj_oid(in): Object Identifier
4489  * tpl(in): Tuple
4490  * dbval(out): Set to the value resulting from the fetch operation
4491  *
4492  * This routine uses the value description indicated by the regulator variable
4493  * to fetch the indicated value and store it in the dbval parameter.
4494  * The value may be fetched from either a heap file object instance,
4495  * or from a list file tuple, or from an all constants regulator variable
4496  * content. If the value is fetched from a heap file object instance,
4497  * then tpl parameter should be given NULL. Likewise, if the value is fetched
4498  * from a list file tuple, then obj_oid parameter should be given NULL.
4499  * If the value is fetched from all constant values referred to
4500  * by the regulator variable, then all of the parameters obj_oid,
4501  * tpl should be given NULL values.
4502  *
4503  * If the value description in the regulator variable refers other cases
4504  * such as constant value, arithmetic expression, the resultant value
4505  * is computed and stored in the db_value.
4506  *
4507  * see fetch_peek_dbval().
4508  */
4509 int
4510 fetch_copy_dbval (THREAD_ENTRY * thread_p, REGU_VARIABLE * regu_var, VAL_DESCR * vd, OID * class_oid, OID * obj_oid,
4511  QFILE_TUPLE tpl, DB_VALUE * dbval)
4512 {
4513  int result;
4514  DB_VALUE *readonly_val, copy_val, *tmp;
4515 
4516  db_make_null (&copy_val);
4517 
4518  result = fetch_peek_dbval (thread_p, regu_var, vd, class_oid, obj_oid, tpl, &readonly_val);
4519  if (result != NO_ERROR)
4520  {
4521  return result;
4522  }
4523 
4524  /*
4525  * This routine needs to ensure that a copy happens. If readonly_val
4526  * points to the same db_value as dbval, qdata_copy_db_value() won't copy.
4527  * This can happen with scans that are PEEKING and routines that
4528  * are sending the COPY flag to fetch_val_list() like the group by
4529  * code. If this happens we use a stack variable for the copy and
4530  * then transfer ownership to the returned dbval
4531  */
4532  if (dbval == readonly_val)
4533  {
4534  tmp = &copy_val;
4535  }
4536  else
4537  {
4538  tmp = dbval;
4539  }
4540 
4541  if (!qdata_copy_db_value (tmp, readonly_val))
4542  {
4543  result = ER_FAILED;
4544  }
4545 
4546  if (tmp == &copy_val)
4547  {
4548  /*
4549  * transfer ownership to the real db_value via a
4550  * structure copy. Make sure you clear the previous value.
4551  */
4552  pr_clear_value (dbval);
4553  *dbval = *tmp;
4554  }
4555 
4556  return result;
4557 }

4559 /*
4560  * fetch_val_list () - fetches all the values for the given regu variable list
4561  * return: NO_ERROR or ER_code
4562  * regu_list(in/out): Regulator Variable list
4563  * vd(in): Value Descriptor
4564  * class_oid(in): Class Identifier
4565  * obj_oid(in): Object Identifier
4566  * tpl(in): Tuple
4567  * peek(int):
4568  */
4569 int
4570 fetch_val_list (THREAD_ENTRY * thread_p, REGU_VARIABLE_LIST regu_list, VAL_DESCR * vd, OID * class_oid, OID * obj_oid,
4571  QFILE_TUPLE tpl, int peek)
4572 {
4573  REGU_VARIABLE_LIST regup;
4574  QFILE_TUPLE next_tpl;
4575  int rc, pos, next_pos;
4576  DB_VALUE *tmp;
4577 
4578  if (peek)
4579  {
4580  next_tpl = tpl + QFILE_TUPLE_LENGTH_SIZE;
4581  next_pos = 0;
4582 
4583  for (regup = regu_list; regup != NULL; regup = regup->next)
4584  {
4585  if (regup->value.type == TYPE_POSITION)
4586  {
4587  pos = regup->value.value.pos_descr.pos_no;
4588  if (pos >= next_pos)
4589  {
4590  pos -= next_pos;
4591  next_pos = regup->value.value.pos_descr.pos_no + 1;
4592  }
4593  else
4594  {
4595  next_tpl = tpl + QFILE_TUPLE_LENGTH_SIZE;
4596  next_pos = 0;
4597  }
4598 
4599  /* at fetch_peek_dbval_pos(), regup->value.vfetch_to is cleared */
4600  rc = fetch_peek_dbval_pos (&regup->value, next_tpl, pos, &tmp, &next_tpl);
4601  }
4602  else
4603  {
4604  if (pr_is_set_type (DB_VALUE_DOMAIN_TYPE (regup->value.vfetch_to)))
4605  {
4606  pr_clear_value (regup->value.vfetch_to);
4607  }
4608  rc = fetch_peek_dbval (thread_p, &regup->value, vd, class_oid, obj_oid, tpl, &tmp);
4609  }
4610 
4611  if (rc != NO_ERROR)
4612  {
4613  pr_clear_value (regup->value.vfetch_to);
4614  return ER_FAILED;
4615  }
4616 
4617  PR_SHARE_VALUE (tmp, regup->value.vfetch_to);
4618  }
4619  }
4620  else
4621  {
4622  /*
4623  * These DB_VALUES must persist across object fetches, so we must
4624  * use fetch_copy_dbval and NOT peek here.
4625  */
4626  for (regup = regu_list; regup != NULL; regup = regup->next)
4627  {
4628  if (pr_is_set_type (DB_VALUE_DOMAIN_TYPE (regup->value.vfetch_to)))
4629  {

4631  }
4632  if (fetch_copy_dbval (thread_p, &regup->value, vd, class_oid, obj_oid, tpl, regup->value.vfetch_to) !=
4633  NO_ERROR)
4634  {
4635  return ER_FAILED;
4636  }
4637  }
4638  }
4639 
4640  return NO_ERROR;
4641 }
